The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Layers (CLs) in computer vision, which is a key topic in the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new type of layer called Shift Attention Layers (SALs), which involves the use of attention mechanisms, a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the reduction of parameters and computations, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
